    <p>Ceolwynn is Ceolmundâ€™s quiet, gentle daughter. She is far more comfortable with music than with conversation and prefers to express herself through the haunting melodies of her hurdy-gurdy.</p>
    <p>Petite and delicate in presence, Ceolwynn has soft brown eyes and a light, careful touch that mirrors her reserved nature. She dresses simply in earthy tones that reflect her modest temperament and wears a small pendant that once belonged to her mother.</p>
    <p>Quiet, kind, and deeply empathetic, Ceolwynn often drifts to the edges of gatherings, listening rather than speaking. Her music, however, reaches everyone: it brings warmth and solace to the crew, soothing frayed nerves and lifting weary hearts.</p>
    <p>Her gentle spirit connects her to others in ways words never could, and many sailors come to see her as the emotional heart of any voyage she joins.</p>
